    <text>
        <body>
            <div type="enclosed">
                <table>
                    <row>
                        <cell>
                            <list>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0583">E. of Kinnoull</persName>.</item>
                                <item>✓ <persName ref="pe0091">of Leven</persName>.</item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0158">Rev<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Macintyre</persName>.</item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0203">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Mackenzie</persName> of <placeName ref="pl0287">Delvin</placeName></item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0022">D<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Ramsay</persName>.</item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0020">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Oliphant</persName></item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0018">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Jackson</persName>.</item>
                            </list>
                        </cell>
                        <cell>
                            <list>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0168">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Marshal</persName> of <placeName ref="pl0094">Perth</placeName>.</item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0207">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Oswald</persName> of <placeName ref="pl0363">Kirkaldie</placeName></item>
                                <item><persName ref="pe1117">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Provost
                                        Christie</persName>
                                    <placeName ref="pl0323">Montrose</placeName>.</item>
                                <item><persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Pope</persName> of <placeName ref="pl1771">Reay</placeName></item>
                                <item>✓<persName ref="pe0228">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Paton</persName></item>
                                <item><persName ref="pe0181">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi>
                                        Barclay</persName> of <placeName ref="pl0330">urie</placeName></item>
                                <item>✓some small parcels of prints.</item>
                            </list>
                        </cell>
                    </row>
                </table>
               <note type="editorial">The ticks next to the above names were presumably added by
                    George Paton to record who had received their books.</note>
            </div>
            <div type="letter">
                <opener><salute>Dear Sir</salute></opener>

                <p>Excuse the trouble of taking under y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> charge the
                    above books which will be sent for. accept also a copy for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> self. only if opportunity offers forward that to
                        <persName ref="pe0246">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Pope</persName>. Pray
                    put the inclosed into the Post. I am much obliged to you for y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> attention to <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0209">the map</title></bibl> &amp; very happy to hear there is
                    such zeal about scotch topography I believe I owe you some trifle before the
                    subscription to the maps. Please to inform me. I am very happy in a letter from
                        <persName ref="pe0156">M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Low</persName>. I hear
                    he is much restored; but I gave him a strict caution about hazarding his health
                    again by too strict an application.</p>
                <p>I am at this instant uncertain whether <persName ref="pe0026">White</persName>
                    can publish my <bibl type="authorial"><title ref="bi0020">Br.
                        Zool.</title></bibl> this season by reason of the shameful delay of the
                        <persName ref="pe1118">Warrington Printer</persName>. The moment it comes
                    out you shall have a set.</p>
                <closer><salute>I am, Dear Sir, y<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> affect. humble
                            Serv<hi rend="superscript">t</hi></salute>
                    <signed><persName ref="pe0232">Tho. Pennant.</persName></signed>

                <dateline><placeName ref="pl0001">Downing</placeName> May 24<hi rend="superscript">th.</hi> 1776.</dateline></closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
